snippet.textDisplay: It's been 13 years since Wild Arms 5 released and that just makes me sad, especially because a JRPG set in a Western setting is still pretty unique to this day. I also feel like each game in the series had its own unique feel, including Wild Arms 2. That and the fact that a composer like Naruke hasn't been really active for all this time is such a waste of talent. There's a simple joy to her compositions.

snippet.textDisplay: I have to thank you very much: YOU are the one that introduced me to this series. I then played the first two games and they have been some of the absolute best JRPGs I've ever played, with part 2 currently being my favorite of the series (I will definitely try out the other parts soon). They really have something unique about them that you won't find on other JRPGs. I especially love the Western setting of the games. It's something completely different compared to that 0815 fantasy setting you have in pretty much every other JRPGs.
